knight fellowships the future of documentary television knight fellowships the future of documentary television reaching out to new audiences marcus herbert 2010 knight fellow executive producer factual programmes british broadcasting corp glasgow united kingdom marcus herbert explored the challenges facing television documentary makers working in science and other knowledge based genres such as history the arts or public affairs that are socially important but threatened by shrinking budgets and changing patterns of media consumption how can we use new technologies to better engage with audiences and how can we adapt the traditional narrative forms of linear television for the digital age the future of factual television meeting the challenge of the digital age marcus herbert's fellowship bio contact herbert at marcus marcusherbert com stanford university
